```markdown
# AI SDK - PixelArt Provider

The **PixelArt provider** for the [AI SDK](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs) contains support for PixelArt's pixel art image generation models.

## Setup

The PixelArt provider is available in the `@ai-sdk/pixelart` module. You can install it with:

\`\`\`bash
npm i @ai-sdk/pixelart
\`\`\`

## Provider Instance

You can import the default provider instance `pixelart` from `@ai-sdk/pixelart`:

\`\`\`ts
import { pixelart } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';
\`\`\`

## Image Generation Example

\`\`\`ts
import { pixelart } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';
import { generateImage } from 'ai';
import fs from 'fs';

const { image } = await generateImage({
  model: pixelart.image('pixel-art-v1'),
  prompt: 'A retro spaceship in a pixel art style',
  providerOptions: {
    pixelart: {
      style: '8bit',
      pixelDensity: 16,
    },
  },
});

const filename = `image-${Date.now()}.png`;
fs.writeFileSync(filename, image.uint8Array);
console.log(`Image saved to ${filename}`);
\`\`\`

## Documentation

Please check out the **[AI SDK docs](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs)** for more information.
